verses.text:
Then said I, Ah, Lord \nd GOD\nd*! surely thou hast greatly
deceived this people and Jerusalem, saying, Ye shall have peace;
whereas the sword reacheth unto the soul.

Hear now this, O foolish people, and without understanding;
which have eyes, and see not; which have ears, and hear not:\f + \fr 5.21 
\ft understanding: Heb. heart\f*

And now, because ye have done all these works, saith the \nd LORD\nd*,
and I spake unto you, rising up early and speaking, but ye heard
not; and I called you, but ye answered not;

Yea, the stork in the heaven knoweth her appointed times; and the
turtle and the crane and the swallow observe the time of their coming;
but my people know not the judgment of the \nd LORD\nd*.

And I will make Jerusalem heaps, \add and\add* a den of dragons;
and I will make the cities of Judah desolate, without an inhabitant.\f + \fr 9.11 
\ft desolate: Heb. desolation\f*

And the \nd LORD\nd* saith, Because they have forsaken my
law which I set before them, and have not obeyed my voice, neither
walked therein;

And first I will recompense their iniquity and their sin double;
because they have defiled my land, they have filled mine inheritance
with the carcases of their detestable and abominable things.

¶ Thus said the \nd LORD\nd* unto me; Go and stand in the gate
of the children of the people, whereby the kings of Judah come in,
and by the which they go out, and in all the gates of Jerusalem;

Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*; Take heed to yourselves, and
bear no burden on the sabbath day, nor bring \add it\add* in by the
gates of Jerusalem;

And it shall come to pass, if ye diligently hearken unto me,
saith the \nd LORD\nd*, to bring in no burden through the gates of this
city on the sabbath day, but hallow the sabbath day, to do no work therein;

I will scatter them as with an east wind before the enemy;
I will shew them the back, and not the face, in the day of their
calamity.

Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*, Go and get a potter’s earthen
bottle, and \add take\add* of the ancients of the people, and of the
ancients of the priests;

For since I spake, I cried out, I cried violence and spoil;
because the word of the \nd LORD\nd* was made a reproach unto me, and a
derision, daily.

And let that man be as the cities which the \nd LORD\nd* overthrew,
and repented not: and let him hear the cry in the morning, and the
shouting at noontide;

¶ Woe unto him that buildeth his house by unrighteousness,
and his chambers by wrong; \add that\add* useth his neighbour’s service
without wages, and giveth him not for his work;

\add As\add* I live, saith the \nd LORD\nd*, though Coniah
the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah were the signet upon my right
hand, yet would I pluck thee thence;

And I will gather the remnant of my flock out of all countries
whither I have driven them, and will bring them again to their folds;
and they shall be fruitful and increase.

How long shall \add this\add* be in the heart of the prophets
that prophesy lies? yea, \add they are\add* prophets of the deceit
of their own heart;

The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the people of
Judah in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah, that
\add was\add* the first year of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon;

Yet ye have not hearkened unto me, saith the \nd LORD\nd*;
that ye might provoke me to anger with the works of your hands to your own
hurt.

And thou shalt say unto them, Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*;
If ye will not hearken to me, to walk in my law, which I have set
before you,

To hearken to the words of my servants the prophets, whom I
sent unto you, both rising up early, and sending \add them\add*,
but ye have not hearkened;

And when Jehoiakim the king, with all his mighty men, and all the
princes, heard his words, the king sought to put him to death: but when
Urijah heard it, he was afraid, and fled, and went into Egypt;

Which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon took not, when he carried away
captive Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah from Jerusalem
to Babylon, and all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem;

¶ Then the word of the \nd LORD\nd* came unto Jeremiah \add the
prophet\add*, after that Hananiah the prophet had broken the yoke
from off the neck of the prophet Jeremiah, saying,

Go and tell Hananiah, saying, Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*;
Thou hast broken the yokes of wood; but thou shalt make for them
yokes of iron.

Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel, unto all that are carried away
captives, whom I have caused to be carried away from Jerusalem unto
Babylon;

For Zedekiah king of Judah had shut him up, saying, Wherefore dost thou
prophesy, and say, Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*, Behold, I will give
this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he shall take it;

For thus saith the \nd LORD\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel;
Houses and fields and vineyards shall be possessed again in this
land.

Which hast set signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, \add even\add*
unto this day, and in Israel, and among \add other\add* men; and hast
made thee a name, as at this day;

And hast brought forth thy people Israel out of the land of
Egypt with signs, and with wonders, and with a strong hand, and with a stretched
out arm, and with great terror;

For thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*, the God of Israel, concerning the
houses of this city, and concerning the houses of the kings of Judah,
which are thrown down by the mounts, and by the sword;

Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*; If ye can break my covenant of the
day, and my covenant of the night, and that there should not be day
and night in their season;

\add Then\add* may also my covenant be broken with David my
servant, that he should not have a son to reign upon his throne;
and with the Levites the priests, my ministers.

Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*; If my covenant \add be\add* not with
day and night, \add and if\add* I have not appointed the ordinances
of heaven and earth;

¶ \add This is\add* the word that came unto Jeremiah from the
\nd LORD\nd*, after that the king Zedekiah had made a covenant with all the
people which \add were\add* at Jerusalem, to proclaim liberty unto them;

The princes of Judah, and the princes of Jerusalem, the eunuchs,
and the priests, and all the people of the land, which passed between the
parts of the calf;

Thus have we obeyed the voice of Jonadab the son of Rechab
our father in all that he hath charged us, to drink no wine all our
days, we, our wives, our sons, nor our daughters;

And it came to pass in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son
of Josiah king of Judah, \add that\add* this word came unto Jeremiah
from the \nd LORD\nd*, saying,

¶ Now when Ebed-melech the Ethiopian, one of the eunuchs which was in the
king’s house, heard that they had put Jeremiah in the dungeon; the
king then sitting in the gate of Benjamin;

Be not afraid of the king of Babylon, of whom ye are afraid;
be not afraid of him, saith the \nd LORD\nd*: for I \add am\add*
with you to save you, and to deliver you from his hand.

But Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the
forces, took all the remnant of Judah, that were returned from all
nations, whither they had been driven, to dwell in the land of Judah;

Take great stones in thine hand, and hide them in the clay
in the brickkiln, which \add is\add* at the entry of Pharaoh’s house
in Tahpanhes, in the sight of the men of Judah;

For in the going up of Luhith continual weeping shall go up;
for in the going down of Horonaim the enemies have heard a cry of
destruction.\f + \fr 48.5  \ft continual…: Heb. weeping with weeping\f*

¶ Concerning Kedar, and concerning the kingdoms of Hazor, which
Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon shall smite, thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*;
Arise ye, go up to Kedar, and spoil the men of the east.

With thee also will I break in pieces man and woman; and with thee will I break in
pieces old and young; and with thee will I break in pieces the young
man and the maid;

One post shall run to meet another, and one messenger to meet
another, to shew the king of Babylon that his city is taken at \add one\add*
end,

And burned the house of the \nd LORD\nd*, and the king’s house;
and all the houses of Jerusalem, and all the houses of the great
\add men\add*, burned he with fire:
